Thx <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fester@lighttanksofdaoc>Fester</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#000000>(6/25/03 1:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=267.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hi new to daoc, advices plz</span><hr size=1> Do you have some more information about yourself? What level are you?  If you are a Highlander then I would recommend that you go slash. Your choice of skills should either be a final goal of 50DW/50Slash/28 Parry or 50DW/44 Slash/37 Parry. I lean towards the 2nd  list as that is my preference but its up to you.<br>
<br>
Post some more questions you have and people will answer. The more specific the better off in getting good answers you will have.<br>
<br>
If you want to look for quests, go to daoc.warcry.com/quests and they have all the quests listed there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tatsumaruiii>TatsumaruIII</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.theotaku.com/trigun/pictures/trigun12/Simage_12.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 151<br> <font color=#000000>(6/26/03 6:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=267.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.theotaku.com/trigun/pictures/trigun12/Simage_12.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hi new to daoc, advices plz</span><hr size=1> Realm Abilities (lots of these are things most tanks should get if they can):<br>
<br>
Determination 2 or 3. Mythic gave us this because we have lots of trouble against magic users (as every tank does). This cuts down on mezzes/stuns/roots by 15% per level, a must have. Det 2 or 3 are the common stops, but if you really like it, take it higher. It's cheaper for us, because we're tanks, so  1 for det 1, 3 for det 2, 6 for det 3, ect.<br>
<br>
Ignore Pain: This one is more of a toss-up. It's a free full heal, can be used in combat, every 30 minutes. Very awesome when you want to try soloing some stealthers or you just &quot;need&quot; a heal and there's no clerics/friars by. The downside, requires First Aid 2 (First Aid refills a set amount of your life when used. Has to be used out of combat, meaning about 7 seconds after hitting someone or you getting hit. Costs about 3 for the first, 6 for the second. The first one heals about 25%, the second heals about 50%. It's -ok-, but mostly got so you can get IP). Costs 8 to get. I love it, most people do, but it's not for everyone.<br>
<br>
Purge: Completly removes any/all negatives effects currently on you. It's like a cleric casting Cure Poisen and Cure Disease on you, aswell as whatever removes Snars, Mezzes, Stuns, ect. Every 15 minutes, so it's gonna be up for a good amount of your fights. If you want to take stealthers, this in conjunction with IP makes you a freakin' machine. Sometimes, you just gotta break that mez. Extremly suggested.<br>
<br>
Mastery Ofs: Mastery of Parry is a must. even if you don't care about parry (for whatever crazy reason). It's only 1 point for MoP 1, 3 for MoP2, and so on. Same for Mastery of Pain, just increases your crit chance instead of parry chance. We also have access to Dodger, which does the same just increases our evade (Something we do once every full moon. I'd maybe get one or even two if I really wanted to evade every 20 minutes). Mo Parry/Pain = Aug Dex 2, Dodger = Aug Quick 2. Suggested to take parry and pain to 1 at least, 2 if you like 'em, 3 if you really like 'em. Not really worth past that. Dodger is much more iffy, and i'd only suggest dodger one if you really want it. 2 if you want, 3+ if you're a die-hard wishing you rolled an Inf <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Each one increases the spec as if we trained 6 more points into it (albiet, we don't actually gain 6 points, but 6 points worth).<br>
<br>
Avoidence Of Magic: Increases the resists to every spell by 3%. Very handy, i'd get the first just because it's a point, and we hate spells <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Going higher would also be a smart move, but you only need the first.<br>
<br>
Dualist's Reflexes: Increases your chance to duel wield by 3% per level. Even at a spec of 50+, this goes directly to your DW chance and not the spec, meaning you will have 3% more DW on top of whatever your spec is. We need to take advantage of our offhand, since it's the most important thing we can do. More it hits, the better we are.<br>
<br>
Interesting abilities (Here's where you get to be uniqe from other mercenarys. The last list was things you should highly consider purchasing. This list are things that work like they should, and will make you better at whatever it does, aswell as over-all. None of these are as required as the last, but since you'll have plenty of RPs left to spend, might aswell take advantage. Gives us flavor, too).<br>
<br>
All the Augmented stats. More of the basics can only be a good thing, and most likly you'll need to spec in a few if you want some of the earlier suggested realm abilities.<br>
<br>
Longwind 1 is noticeable, and can help you when you really want to sprint longer. Would suggest to keep it at 1 though, as many report the next 4 make extremly little difference. Only one point, what's the harm? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Tireless regenerates an alright amount. Basicly, if you stand around, you gain endurance slowly. if you move, you stop gainning end. This allows you to gain end as you move, which is good in RvR since you never want to sit, and most likly will always be moving. During combat, i'd say about another swing worth of end, but varies on what styles you're using.<br>
<br>
Toughness increases your max HP by 3% per level. At any level, this ability will follow you through all levels. such as, at level 25, you'll have 3% more HP then someone of the same class/race/level without this ability. Same for any other level (30, 40, 45, ect). More HP helps a bunch, and one point for 3% more HP is great.<br>
<br>
Lifter allows you to carry 20% more weight then normal. If you find yourself carrying lots of stuff (maybe you like making Rams or other seige equipment) then this will prove helpfull. Otherwise, it's of no interest.<br>
<br>
Prevent Flight is great for stopping people from running from you. Often healers, casters and other support types who don't fight will hit you with some sort of CC (root, mez, stun) and then run. If you resist these (which can happen an acceptable amount), they're going to hit sprint, then run in a random direction. They'll have more end then you most likly, since they don't go around beating people up. They will out-run you, unless you stop them in their tracks. This has a 35% chance to proc while hitting their backs, for a 50% unbreakable snare that lasts ten seconds. Perfect for catching those buggers. Very suggested, but costs a hefty amount of points; 14.<br>
<br>
Trip/Grapple work, and they're pretty nice. Point Blank Area Of Effects, meaning anyone close to you. Trip snares for 30% of their speed in a radius for 12 seconds. Grapple does the same, but roots instead of slows. Not many use it, but it can be very effective. I'm not sure if the root/snare is breakable, but most likly is.<br>
<br>
Whirling Dervish seems to work. 5% increase to DW for 60 seconds on the first level, 10% on the second. For the cost, not worth it to me. But might be for you.<br>
<br>
Rain Ofs abilities (spirit, fire, ice, ect) are pretty good for some more damage. 10% more damage of the damage types (dependent on the kind you get) per level. Useable every 15 minutes. Not bad. It functions, so that means it feasable if it appeals to you.<br>
<br>
The Empty Mind, gives you a 10% increase to all your resists for 60 seconds, useable every 15 minutes. More resists are only good, and i only wish it lasted forever <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  don't have it myself, but still worth the points.<br>
<br>
Second Wind works, but a full end bar.. well, your choice. Rather beg the pally to group with me for a few seconds.<br>
<br>
Realm Abilities You Should Avoid! (These are ablities that broken, or function very poorly)<br>
<br>
Regeneration: gives you back very little life. You won't notice it, no matter the level. Even one point isn't a good investment.<br>
<br>
Mastery of Water: 3% more movement speed in water. Would be nice, sep for one tiny little setback - There's an extreme draught in every frontier (the places you go for level 50 RvR). There are water spots, but they're so far away you're never going to get to them, let alone need to swim in them (most have level50+ aggro mobs!). bad investment, even for the first.<br>
<br>
Veil Recovery: Reduces rez sickness time. Very useless.. not much else <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Mastery of Arms: broken. otherwise, would be good. makes you swing faster. Can't go wrong there.. oh wait, it's already gone wrong <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Bladedance: Does very little damage for the points. Maybe for interupting.. -maybe-. would rather stay away from it.<br>
<br>
Hail of Blows: Broken. Would be -ok-, but is broken so far. Doesn't look like getting fixed anytime soon.<br>
<br>
Void: Our special RA uniqe to us. The damage is about that of Duel Shadows, but with a timer. Not worth it, at least, not until it gets changed.<br>
<br>
Lots of realm abilites, even with a couple broken/useless ones.<br>
<br>
Hope it helps <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>&quot;We will never be what Mythic promised we would when DAoC started, we might as well adapt or delete.&quot; -Avandor<br>
Lothire - 50 Mercenary<br>
